Addresses five gaps observed in the 42-video "2026ClaudeCode活用術"
run where the output was too abstract for a hands-on document.

P1 (Leader) — `## 核心要素` now requires `(出典: [[...#^MM-SS]])` on
every numbered item, not just the `## 概念定義` block. Multi-video
items list up to 3 citations separated by `;`.

P2 (Leader) — forbids the `A→B→C→D` anti-pattern that compressed
whole pipelines into a single sentence (e.g. Superpowers' 7 steps).
Arrow chains of 3+ steps must be expanded into independent bullets
with 1-2 sentences of state per step (input / trigger / output).

P3 (β) — each chapter must have ≥5 topics. `unique` chapters could
previously ship with 2-3 thin items; β now either merges thin
chapters or promotes them to `supporting`.

P4 (Leader) — MOC gets a `## 概念別索引` table (`| 概念 | 章 |`)
so readers can look up "where does X appear" without scanning all
chapter bodies.

P5 (Leader) — `## 学習順序の推奨` must contain three explicit reader
intent courses: 全章通読 / 30 分で要点把握 / 深掘り. Generic prose
("read chapter 1 first") is no longer sufficient.

Tests: `test_synthesis_prompt_rules.py` (8 new) locks in the exact
strings so future edits can't silently drop the rules. Regression
assertions guard existing constraints (JSON-only, image fabrication
ban, Obsidian-unsafe filename chars).

Total: 553 → 561 passed.

